t%2045%20minutes%20after%20she%20went%20overboard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202022%2C%20Carnival%20Valor%20cruise%20ship%20passenger%20James%20Michael%20Grimes%20survived%20after%20going%20overboard%2C%20unbeknownst%20to%20anyone%20on%20board%2C%20and%20spending%2020%20hours%20in%20the%20water%20in%20what%20he%20described%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fman-fell-off-cruise-ship-ate-bamboo-fought-off-jellyfish-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efight%20for%20his%20life%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20described%20treading%20water%2C%20fending%20off%20jellyfish%20and%20at%20least%20one%20finned%20creature%2C%20and%20trying%20to%20eat%20objects%20that%20floated%20by%2C%20including%20a%20piece%20of%20bamboo.%20He%20was%20finally%20spotted%20and%20rescued%20by%20the%20US%20Coast%20Guard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20practical%20things%20a%20person%20who%20falls%20into%20the%20open%20ocean%20can%20do%20in%20order%20to%20increase%20their%20chances%20of%20surviving%2C%20according%20to%20Cat%20Bigney%2C%20a%20survival%20expert%20who%20has%20consulted%20for%20Bear%20Grylls%20and%20National%20Geographic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222a1f46eb-54a5-4b32-8875-e6147a2f7ac4%5C%22%3EDon't%20panic%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20things%20working%20against%20a%20person%20who%20goes%20overboard.%20First%2C%20they%20have%20to%20avoid%20injury%20during%20the%20fall%20and%20when%20they%20hit%20the%20water.%20Calling%20for%20help%20or%20actually%20finding%20help%20in%20the%20open%20ocean%20is%20just%20about%20impossible.%20There%20could%20be%20blazing%20sun%2C%20potentially%20hungry%20predators%2C%20and%20rough%20water.%20Hypothermia%20and%20dehydration%20are%20also%20major%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20these%20factors%20make%20it%20very%20difficult%20for%20people%20to%20survive%20if%20they're%20adrift%2C%26quot%3B%20Bigney%2C%20who%20has%20taught%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.boss-inc.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoulder%20Outdoor%20Survival%20School%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20decades%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20overboard%20on%20a%20cruise%20ship%20is%20extremely%20rare%2C%20but%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20those%20who%20do%20are%20never%20rescued.%20Between%202009%20and%202019%2C%20there%20were%20212%20overboard%20incidents%20on%20cruise%20ships%2C%20according%20to%20data%20compiled%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcruising.org%2F-%2Fmedia%2Fresearch-updates%2Freport_operational_incidents_2019-v-1.ashx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECruise%20Lines%20International%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Only%2048%20of%20those%20people%20were%20rescued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20first%20thing%20a%20person%20in%20an%20overboard%20situation%20needs%20to%20remember%20is%3F%20Don't%20panic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20enter%20into%20a%20body%20of%20water%2C%20they%20usually%20damage%20their%20lungs%20right%20away%2C%20because%20they%20gasp%2C%26quot%3B%20Bigney%20explained.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20such%20a%20panic%20instinct%20to%20get%20air%2C%20and%20when%20people%20do%20that%20they%20bring%20water%20into%20their%20lungs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20your%20cool%20in%20life-or-death%20situations%20is%20key%2C%20as%20panicking%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurvival-expert-explains-how-woman-survived-in-utah-national-forest-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bthe%20biggest%20thing%20that%20will%20kill%20you%20in%20a%20survival%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0according%20to%20Bigney.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221258%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Carnival%20Valor%20ship%20in%20Grand%20Cayman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6395687ba3bebb0018b3f95a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22629%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECarnival%20Valor%2C%20pictured%20here%20in%202010%2C%20was%20re-routed%20to%20Mobile%2C%20Alabama%20this%20week%20as%20the%20Port%20of%20New%20Orleans%20shuttered%20for%20the%20arrival%20of%20tropical%20storm%20Barry.%3Cp%3E(AP%20Photo%2FJ%20Pat%20Carte%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d10a064-3550-4db4-b886-3f1310b0d5f7%5C%22%3EFind%20anything%20that%20floats%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you're%20in%20open%20water%2C%20your%20next%20priority%20is%20to%20stay%20above%20the%20surface.%20Some%20people%20may%20have%20a%20natural%20advantage%20and%20float%20more%20easily%2C%20depending%20on%20their%20body%20composition%2C%20including%20body%20fat%20percentage%20and%20muscle%20mass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Grimes%20was%20in%20the%20water%20for%20around%2020%20hours%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20he%20was%20treading%20water%20for%20that%20entire%20time%2C%20according%20to%20Bigney.%20A%20combination%20of%20floating%2C%20treading%2C%20and%20swimming%20would%20be%20ideal%2C%20although%20it%20would%20still%20be%20exhausting%2C%20especially%20in%20rough%20waters.%20But%20treading%20water%20periodically%20is%20still%20much%20more%20doable%20than%20constantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20ways%20to%20make%20floating%20easier.%20For%20instance%2C%20Grimes%20said%20he%20had%20taken%20off%20all%20of%20his%20clothes%2C%20in%20order%20to%20make%20himself%20more%20buoyant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20a%20small%20buoyant%20device%20will%20help%20you%20%E2%80%94%20something%20you%20can%20use%20with%20your%20arms%20around%20or%20your%20neck%20over%20just%20to%20help%20relieve%20some%20of%20the%20stress%20if%20you're%20not%20a%20great%20swimmer%20or%20you're%20having%20a%20hard%20time%20staying%20afloat%2C%26quot%3B%20Bigney%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrimes%20had%20said%20he%20tried%20chewing%20on%20some%20bamboo%2C%20which%20Bigney%20said%20is%20extremely%20buoyant.%20Even%20collecting%20small%20bits%20of%20bamboo%20or%20driftwood%20could%20help%20a%20person%20stay%20afloat%2C%20she%20said.%20In%20a%20best-case%20scenario%2C%20you%20could%20collect%20enough%20that%20would%20allow%20you%20to%20make%20a%20pile%20or%20raft%20that%20you%20could%20get%20up%20on%20top%20of%20and%20out%20of%20the%20water%2C%20which%20would%20also%20make%20you%20safer%20from%20any%20potential%20predators.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22401bd220-27fc-40af-bfa4-c9c9fbe69eab%5C%22%3EWater%20would%20be%20a%20concern%2C%20food%20not%20so%20much%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unlikely%20Grimes%20was%20able%20to%20get%20significant%20energy%20from%20chewing%20on%20bamboo%2C%20but%20food%20would%20not%20be%20a%20primary%20concern%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20he%20was%20at%20sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20bodies%20are%20perfectly%2C%20evolutionarily%20adapted%20to%20have%20this%20ability%20to%20fast%20for%20a%20long%20period%20of%20time%2C%20so%20he%20should%20have%20been%20fine%20as%20far%20as%20food%2C%26quot%3B%20Bigney%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bpsychologically%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20may%20have%20helped%20him%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bphysiologically%26quot%3B%20his%20body%20was%20probably%20OK%20without%20eating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalories%20are%20needed%20to%20regulate%20core%20body%20temperatures%2C%20but%20she%20said%20most%20bodies%20would%20be%20able%20to%20do%20that%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20with%20reserves%2C%20including%20from%20fat%20and%20the%20liver.%20Grimes%20was%20treated%20for%20hypothermia%20after%20he%20was%20rescued%2C%20as%20the%2070-degree%20water%20temperature%20was%20significantly%20colder%20than%20humans'%20baseline%20core%20body%20temperature%2C%20but%20moving%20around%20and%20swimming%20for%20much%20of%20the%20time%20he%20was%20stranded%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20factors%20like%20what%20he%20had%20recently%20eaten%20and%20his%20body%20fat%20content%20%E2%80%94%20may%20have%20helped%20him%20avoid%20the%20worst%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDehydration%20would%20be%20of%20much%20greater%20immediate%20concern%20than%20food%2C%20according%20to%20Bigney.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20to%20drink%20any%20salt%20water%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20you'd%20want%20to%20try%20to%20conserve%20whatever%20water%20you%20already%20had.%20One%20way%20to%20do%20that%20would%20be%20to%20try%20and%20use%20your%20clothing%20to%20create%20shelter%20from%20the%20sun%2C%20such%20as%20by%20wrapping%20it%20over%20your%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223769%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Garbage%20floating%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20sea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63956857c4e31900185d29f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222827%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGarbage%20floating%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20sea%20can%20be%20used%20to%20make%20a%20signal.%3Cp%3EUlrike%20Schmitt-Hartmann%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229bafeecc-dadb-4c85-b501-ea094d1e9bc6%5C%22%3EMake%20a%20signal%20however%20you%20can%20%E2%80%94%20including%20with%20trash%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20if%20you%20fall%20from%20a%20cruise%20ship%20many%20miles%20from%20shore%2C%20it's%20a%20waiting%20game%20to%20be%20rescued%2C%20and%20making%20a%20signal%20is%20one%20way%20to%20improve%20your%20chances%20of%20being%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20trash%20in%20our%20great%20oceans%2C%20unfortunately%2C%26quot%3B%20Bigney%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20collecting%20any%20floating%20garbage%20into%20a%20large%20pile%20could%20potentially%20form%20a%20signal%20that%20could%20be%20spotted%20by%20rescuers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%C2%A0overboard%20situation%20is%20reported%2C%20the%20US%20Coast%20Guard%20uses%20a%20program%20to%20estimate%20where%20a%20floating%20object%20might%20be%2C%20Gross%20told%20Insider.%20The%20Search%20and%20Rescue%20Optimal%20Planning%20System%20factors%20in%20the%20person's%20weight%2C%20clothing%2C%20body%20fat%20percentage%2C%20and%20whether%20or%20not%20they%20have%20a%20flotation%20device%2C%20as%20well%20as%20weather%20and%20ocean%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Grimes%2C%20the%20system%20returned%20over%207%2C000%20square%20nautical%20miles%20of%20ocean%20where%20he%20could%20be%2C%20which%20is%20about%20the%20size%20of%20Massachusetts%20%E2%80%94%20so%20anything%20you%20can%20do%20to%20increase%20the%20chances%20of%20being%20spotted%20can%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20end%2C%20it's%20kind%20of%20a%20grim%20situation%2C%20but%20people%20have%20survived%2C%26quot%3B%20Bigney%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BAnd%20people%20sometimes%20just%20die.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEditor's%20note%3A%20This%20story%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20December%202022%20and%20was%20last%20updated%20in%20June%202025.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20news%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akvlamis%40insider.com%3Finline-read-more%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ekvlamis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffall-overboard-cruise-ship-what-to-do-survival-tips%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751323408000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63956839a3bebb0018b3f94f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffall-overboard-cruise-ship-what-to-do-survival-tips%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20girl%20and%20her%20father%20were%20rescued%20after%20going%20overboard%20a%20Disney%20cruise%20ship.%20A%20expert%20offers%20survival%20tips%20on%20what%20to%20do%20if%20you%20fall%20overboard.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40businessinsider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A31%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffall-overboard-cruise-ship-what-to-do-survival-tips%22%2C%